Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
On behalf of Property NSW, CBRE are proud to exclusively present Science House – 157-161 Gloucester Street, The Rocks.

A one of a kind opportunity; Science House is widely recognised for its unique, award winning architectural design and significance to Sydney’s history.

+ 95% leased, backed by a quality anchor covenant
+ NLA of 2,075sqm (approx)
+ Value add opportunity with rental reversion 
+ Close to transport inc new George Street Light Rail
+ Walk to Circular Quay
+ 0 Star NABERS Engery Rating

For Sale by way of a Tender process closing at 3:00pm, Thursday 22nd August 2019.

Extensively refurbished in 2007, 117 Harrington Street is a heritage building comprising retail space on the ground level, four commercial levels and a two storey roof-top extension.

Prominently located in the Rocks commercial precinct and only moments to Sydney’s CBD Core, bounded by Harrington, Gloucester and Essex Streets. The building is positioned directly behind Grosvenor Place and less than 100 metres from George Street and within close walking distance to Wynyard rail and bus terminal and Circular Quay.

AVAILABLE FOR LEASE:

- LEVEL 1: Whole floor of some 268sqm. Ground floor access with glass entry doors off Essex Street. Existing fitout includes workstations and partitioned offices. Shared access to communal rooftop terrace.

For more information or to arrange an inspection, please contact Nick Read (0413 853 554) or Tom Bowditch (0424 292 404).

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: HERITAGE OFFICE SPACE – LAST REMAINING FLOOR

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are pleased to offer for sale Suite 212/111 Harrington Street, The Rocks.

Located in the distinguished Quay West Building, this commercial suite is situated in the sought-after northern precinct of the Sydney CBD. The prestigious address presents an excellent opportunity for both owner occupiers and investors alike.

Key features include:
- 61 sqm* commercial suite
- Offered with vacant possession
- Opportunity to occupy or invest
- Walking distance to Wynyard, Circular Quay and The Rocks
- Building facilities include secure parking, accommodation, conference rooms, restaurants and bars

Terms:
- 10% Deposit
- 42 Day Settlement

The property will be sold by way of Public Auction on Tuesday, 27 October 2015 at 10:30AM.

Auction Venue: auctionWORKS, Mezzanine Level, 50 Margaret Street, Sydney 2000

All inspections will be held by appointment only. Please contact the following exclusive agent:

Julian Choo
0430 001 277

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Views of Circular Quay & Opera House

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
88 George Street is a character-rich building in historic The Rocks precinct. The building boasts excellent natural light on three sides, including views of Circular Quay and Sydney Opera House.

Available for lease is a quality fitted whole floor of some 373sqm, comprising: boardroom, meeting rooms and offices, open plan work areas and kitchen breakout.

Unique opportunity to set your business apart from your competitors and enjoy the relaxed village-style atmosphere of The Rocks.

Rich in history and character, The Rocks precinct provides an array of fine restaurants, cafes and retail stores with excellent access to Circular Quay ferry wharfs, train station and light rail.

Please call exclusive leasing agents CBRE for more information.
